# WasatchWise Project Context

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 15 (App Router, Server Actions, React Server Components)
- TypeScript strict mode
- Supabase (Postgres + Auth + Storage)
- Tailwind CSS
- Vercel hosting

## Code Style
- Use functional components (no classes)
- Prefer Server Components (add 'use client' only when needed)
- Use Zod for validation
- Use Server Actions for mutations (avoid API routes unless needed for webhooks)
- Database queries: use Supabase client (not Prisma/Drizzle)

## File Naming
- Components: PascalCase (e.g., `HeroSection.tsx`)
- Actions/utilities: camelCase (e.g., `submitQuiz.ts`)
- Routes: lowercase-with-hyphens (e.g., `ai-readiness-quiz/`)

## AI Integration Patterns
- Claude API: use for text generation, analysis
- HeyGen API: use for personalized videos
- ElevenLabs API: use for voice synthesis
- Always log AI usage to `ai_content_log` table

## Database
- Use Supabase client (not raw SQL in app code)
- Migrations in `supabase/migrations/`
- Enable RLS on all client-facing tables

